  <h1>Agile WSJF Prioritization Framework</h1>
  <p><strong>Weighted Shortest Job First (WSJF)</strong> helps teams prioritize work by dividing <em>Value</em> by <em>Effort</em>. The higher the ratio, the higher the priority.</p>

  <div class="grid-container">

    <!-- Step 1: Cost of Delay Grid -->
    <div class="grid">
      <div class="grid-title">1. Assess Value using COD Grid</div>
      <p><strong>Relative value and urgency</strong></p>
      <table class="grid-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th rowspan="2">Value</th>
            <th colspan="3">Time Criticality</th>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <th>Whenever</th>
            <th>Soon</th>
            <th>ASAP!</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td rowspan="2"><strong>Killer</strong></td>
            <td class="value-cell">Medium (3)</td>
            <td class="value-cell">High (5)</td>
            <td class="value-cell">Very High (8)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="value-cell">Low (2)</td>
            <td class="value-cell">Medium (3)</td>
            <td class="value-cell">High (5)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td rowspan="2"><strong>"Meh"</strong></td>
            <td class="value-cell">Very Low (1)</td>
            <td class="value-cell">Low (1)</td>
            <td class="value-cell">Medium (3)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="value-cell">Very Low (1)</td>
            <td class="value-cell">Low (1)</td>
            <td class="value-cell">Medium (3)</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <p><small><strong>Cost of Delay (COD)</strong>: If delayed a week, this would cost us $x</small></p>
    </div>

    <!-- Step 2: Size Assessment Grid -->
    <div class="grid">
      <div class="grid-title">2. Assess Size</div>
      <p><strong>Relative effort and complexity</strong></p>
      <table class="grid-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Extra Large (8)</th>
            <th>Large (5)</th>
            <th>Medium (3)</th>
            <th>Small (2)</th>
            <th>Extra Small (1)</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td class="size-cell"><div class="sticky-note"></div></td>
            <td class="size-cell"><div class="sticky-note"></div></td>
            <td class="size-cell"><div class="sticky-note"></div></td>
            <td class="size-cell"><div class="sticky-note"></div></td>
            <td class="size-cell"><div class="sticky-note"></div></td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

  </div>

  <!-- WSJF Calculation -->
  <div class="wsjf-section">
    <h2>3. Calculate WSJF Score</h2>
    <div class="wsjf-formula">
      WSJF = <strong>Cost of Delay</strong> ÷ <strong>Size</strong>
    </div>
    <p>Higher score = Higher priority</p>

    <div class="example">
      <strong>Example:</strong><br>
      Feature A: COD = 8, Size = 2 → WSJF = 8 ÷ 2 = <strong>4.0</strong><br>
      Feature B: COD = 5, Size = 5 → WSJF = 5 ÷ 5 = <strong>1.0</strong><br>
      → Feature A has higher priority.
    </div>

